Updated May 4, 2016 9:32 p.m.
ET
Growth has its price at Fitbit.
So does ambition.
When the fitness-band maker introduced its first smartwatch-like product back in January, many wrote it off as a doomed effort to compete against Apple.
The Fitbit Blaze offers far fewer functions at a much lower price than the Apple Watch.
But the image stuck, and subsequent reviews were unflattering.
Fitbit lost half its market value over the following month.
